{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NzrCYe5mrLq4idDaBd5kEf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: PRD-560.3\n3\ttitle: Verify and update invoke.py transcript parsing\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: xs\n8\tcapability: simple\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-560-transcripts-should-be-jsonl-files]]\"\n10\tdepends_on:\n11\t  - \"[[PRD-560.1-rewrite-transcript-assembly-jsonl]]\"\n12\tblocks: []\n13\timpacts:\n14\t  - src/darkfactory/invoke.py\n15\tworkflow:\n16\ttarget_version:\n17\tcreated: 2026-04-09\n18\tupdated: 2026-04-09\n19\ttags: []\n20\t---\n21\t\n22\t# Verify and update invoke.py transcript parsing\n23\t\n24\t## Summary\n25\t\n26\tVerify that `_find_terminal_result` and `_parse_sentinels` in `invoke.py` continue to work correctly with the new JSONL transcript format. The new `darkfactory_metadata`, `darkfactory_section`, and `darkfactory_stderr` envelope lines are valid JSON, so these functions should parse them without error — but they must not be confused for actual sentinel or result data. Update if necessary.\n27\t\n28\t## Requirements\n29\t\n30\t1. Verify that `_find_terminal_result` (~lines 104-343) correctly skips or ignores the new `darkfactory_metadata`, `darkfactory_section`, and `darkfactory_stderr` JSONL lines when searching for the terminal result.\n31\t2. Verify that `_parse_sentinels` correctly skips or ignores the new envelope lines when scanning for sentinel patterns.\n32\t3. If either function would incorrectly match on the new envelope lines, add a filter to exclude lines with `\"type\"` starting with `\"darkfactory_\"`.\n33\t4. Update any `.log` file path references in `invoke.py` to `.jsonl` if present.\n34\t\n35\t## Technical Approach\n36\t\n37\t### File: `src/darkfactory/invoke.py` (~lines 104-343)\n38\t\n39\t1. Read `_find_terminal_result` and trace its logic for each new envelope line type:\n40\t   - `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_metadata\", ...}` — does the function's JSON parsing pick this up? Does it match any result-detection heuristic?\n41\t   - `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", ...}` — same analysis.\n42\t   - `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_stderr\", ...}` — same analysis.\n43\t\n44\t2. Read `_parse_sentinels` and do the same analysis.\n45\t\n46\t3. If either function could misinterpret an envelope line as a meaningful result or sentinel, add an early-continue check:\n47\t   ```python\n48\t   parsed = json.loads(line)\n49\t   if parsed.get(\"type\", \"\").startswith(\"darkfactory_\"):\n50\t       continue\n51\t   ```\n52\t\n53\t4. Search for any `.log` path references and update to `.jsonl`.\n54\t\n55\t## Acceptance Criteria\n56\t\n57\t- [ ] AC-1: `_find_terminal_result` does not misinterpret `darkfactory_*` envelope lines as terminal results.\n58\t- [ ] AC-2: `_parse_sentinels` does not misinterpret `darkfactory_*` envelope lines as sentinels.\n59\t- [ ] AC-3: Existing transcript parsing continues to function correctly with the new JSONL format.\n60\t- [ ] AC-4: Any `.log` path references in `invoke.py` are updated to `.jsonl`.\n61\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3ac8cfa-47e5-4f0b-af2d-2bedae0776fa","uuid":"78281074-127b-4f41-a71e-dc32e01ece1d","timestamp":"2026-04-09T07:53:01.059Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.darkfactory/prds/PRD-560.3-verify-invoke-parsing.md","content":"---\nid: PRD-560.3\ntitle: Verify and update invoke.py transcript parsing\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: xs\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-560-transcripts-should-be-jsonl-files]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-560.1-rewrite-transcript-assembly-jsonl]]\"\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/invoke.py\nworkflow:\ntarget_version:\ncreated: 2026-04-09\nupdated: 2026-04-09\ntags: []\n---\n\n# Verify and update invoke.py transcript parsing\n\n## Summary\n\nVerify that `_find_terminal_result` and `_parse_sentinels` in `invoke.py` continue to work correctly with the new JSONL transcript format. The new `darkfactory_metadata`, `darkfactory_section`, and `darkfactory_stderr` envelope lines are valid JSON, so these functions should parse them without error — but they must not be confused for actual sentinel or result data. Update if necessary.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Verify that `_find_terminal_result` (~lines 104-343) correctly skips or ignores the new `darkfactory_metadata`, `darkfactory_section`, and `darkfactory_stderr` JSONL lines when searching for the terminal result.\n2. Verify that `_parse_sentinels` correctly skips or ignores the new envelope lines when scanning for sentinel patterns.\n3. If either function would incorrectly match on the new envelope lines, add a filter to exclude lines with `\"type\"` starting with `\"darkfactory_\"`.\n4. Update any `.log` file path references in `invoke.py` to `.jsonl` if present.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### File: `src/darkfactory/invoke.py` (~lines 104-343)\n\n1. Read `_find_terminal_result` and trace its logic for each new envelope line type:\n   - `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_metadata\", ...}` — does the function's JSON parsing pick this up? Does it match any result-detection heuristic?\n   - `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", ...}` — same analysis.\n   - `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_stderr\", ...}` — same analysis.\n\n2. Read `_parse_sentinels` and do the same analysis.\n\n3. If either function could misinterpret an envelope line as a meaningful result or sentinel, add an early-continue check:\n   ```python\n   parsed = json.loads(line)\n   if parsed.get(\"type\", \"\").startswith(\"darkfactory_\"):\n       continue\n   ```\n\n4. Search for any `.log` path references and update to `.jsonl`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `_find_terminal_result` does not misinterpret `darkfactory_*` envelope lines as terminal results.\n- [ ] AC-2: `_parse_sentinels` does not misinterpret `darkfactory_*` envelope lines as sentinels.\n- [ ] AC-3: Existing transcript parsing continues to function correctly with the new JSONL format.\n- [ ] AC-4: Any `.log` path references in `invoke.py` are updated to `.jsonl`.\n","numLines":61,"startLine":1,"totalLines":61}}}
