{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XmB76u24GM2qkJ5St1GgW4","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: PRD-560.1\n3\ttitle: Rewrite runner.py transcript assembly to emit JSONL\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: s\n8\tcapability: moderate\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-560-transcripts-should-be-jsonl-files]]\"\n10\tdepends_on: []\n11\tblocks:\n12\t  - \"[[PRD-560.2-update-commit-transcript-extension]]\"\n13\t  - \"[[PRD-560.3-verify-invoke-parsing]]\"\n14\timpacts:\n15\t  - src/darkfactory/runner.py\n16\tworkflow:\n17\ttarget_version:\n18\tcreated: 2026-04-09\n19\tupdated: 2026-04-09\n20\ttags: []\n21\t---\n22\t\n23\t# Rewrite runner.py transcript assembly to emit JSONL\n24\t\n25\t## Summary\n26\t\n27\tReplace the `#`-prefixed metadata and separator lines in `runner.py:_run_agent` (~lines 356-377) with proper JSONL lines, and change the transcript file extension from `.log` to `.jsonl`. This is the core change that makes transcripts valid JSONL from top to bottom.\n28\t\n29\t## Requirements\n30\t\n31\t1. Emit a `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_metadata\", \"task\": \"...\", \"model\": \"...\", \"success\": ..., \"exit_code\": ..., \"failure_reason\": ...}` JSONL line at the top of the transcript instead of the `#`-prefixed metadata comment lines.\n32\t2. Replace the `# ---- stdout ----` separator with a `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", \"section\": \"stdout\"}` JSONL line.\n33\t3. Replace the `# ---- stderr ----` separator with a `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", \"section\": \"stderr\"}` JSONL line.\n34\t4. Wrap stderr content (plain text) in a single `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_stderr\", \"text\": \"...\"}` JSONL line containing the full stderr block.\n35\t5. Write the transcript to `.jsonl` extension instead of `.log` — both the transient path (`.harness-transcripts/{prd_id}.jsonl`) and any path variable used for the committed location.\n36\t\n37\t## Technical Approach\n38\t\n39\t### File: `src/darkfactory/runner.py` (~lines 356-377)\n40\t\n41\tLocate the transcript assembly block in `_run_agent`. Currently it writes lines like:\n42\t\n43\t```python\n44\tf\"# task: {task_name}\\n\"\n45\tf\"# model: {model}\\n\"\n46\tf\"# success: {success}\\n\"\n47\tf\"# exit_code: {exit_code}\\n\"\n48\tf\"# failure_reason: {failure_reason}\\n\"\n49\t\"# ---- stdout ----\\n\"\n50\tresult.stdout\n51\t\"# ---- stderr ----\\n\"\n52\tresult.stderr\n53\t```\n54\t\n55\tReplace with:\n56\t\n57\t```python\n58\timport json\n59\t\n60\tmetadata_line = json.dumps({\n61\t    \"type\": \"darkfactory_metadata\",\n62\t    \"task\": task_name,\n63\t    \"model\": model,\n64\t    \"success\": success,\n65\t    \"exit_code\": exit_code,\n66\t    \"failure_reason\": failure_reason,\n67\t}) + \"\\n\"\n68\t\n69\tstdout_section = json.dumps({\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", \"section\": \"stdout\"}) + \"\\n\"\n70\tstderr_section = json.dumps({\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", \"section\": \"stderr\"}) + \"\\n\"\n71\tstderr_line = json.dumps({\"type\": \"darkfactory_stderr\", \"text\": result.stderr}) + \"\\n\"\n72\t```\n73\t\n74\tThen change the file extension from `.log` to `.jsonl` wherever the transient transcript path is constructed.\n75\t\n76\t## Acceptance Criteria\n77\t\n78\t- [ ] AC-1: Transcripts written by `runner.py` are valid JSONL (every line parses as JSON).\n79\t- [ ] AC-2: Transcript files use `.jsonl` extension in the transient location (`.harness-transcripts/{prd_id}.jsonl`).\n80\t- [ ] AC-3: Metadata (task, model, success, exit_code, failure_reason) is present as a `darkfactory_metadata` JSONL line at the top of the file.\n81\t- [ ] AC-4: Stdout content is preceded by a `darkfactory_section` line with `\"section\": \"stdout\"`.\n82\t- [ ] AC-5: Stderr content is wrapped in a single `darkfactory_stderr` JSONL line.\n83\t- [ ] AC-6: No `#`-prefixed comment lines remain in the transcript output.\n84\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3ac8cfa-47e5-4f0b-af2d-2bedae0776fa","uuid":"68110e24-bca9-4ed6-a256-7475387f3ef3","timestamp":"2026-04-09T07:53:27.097Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.darkfactory/prds/PRD-560.1-rewrite-transcript-assembly-jsonl.md","content":"---\nid: PRD-560.1\ntitle: Rewrite runner.py transcript assembly to emit JSONL\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: moderate\nparent: \"[[PRD-560-transcripts-should-be-jsonl-files]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-560.2-update-commit-transcript-extension]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-560.3-verify-invoke-parsing]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/runner.py\nworkflow:\ntarget_version:\ncreated: 2026-04-09\nupdated: 2026-04-09\ntags: []\n---\n\n# Rewrite runner.py transcript assembly to emit JSONL\n\n## Summary\n\nReplace the `#`-prefixed metadata and separator lines in `runner.py:_run_agent` (~lines 356-377) with proper JSONL lines, and change the transcript file extension from `.log` to `.jsonl`. This is the core change that makes transcripts valid JSONL from top to bottom.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Emit a `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_metadata\", \"task\": \"...\", \"model\": \"...\", \"success\": ..., \"exit_code\": ..., \"failure_reason\": ...}` JSONL line at the top of the transcript instead of the `#`-prefixed metadata comment lines.\n2. Replace the `# ---- stdout ----` separator with a `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", \"section\": \"stdout\"}` JSONL line.\n3. Replace the `# ---- stderr ----` separator with a `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", \"section\": \"stderr\"}` JSONL line.\n4. Wrap stderr content (plain text) in a single `{\"type\": \"darkfactory_stderr\", \"text\": \"...\"}` JSONL line containing the full stderr block.\n5. Write the transcript to `.jsonl` extension instead of `.log` — both the transient path (`.harness-transcripts/{prd_id}.jsonl`) and any path variable used for the committed location.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### File: `src/darkfactory/runner.py` (~lines 356-377)\n\nLocate the transcript assembly block in `_run_agent`. Currently it writes lines like:\n\n```python\nf\"# task: {task_name}\\n\"\nf\"# model: {model}\\n\"\nf\"# success: {success}\\n\"\nf\"# exit_code: {exit_code}\\n\"\nf\"# failure_reason: {failure_reason}\\n\"\n\"# ---- stdout ----\\n\"\nresult.stdout\n\"# ---- stderr ----\\n\"\nresult.stderr\n```\n\nReplace with:\n\n```python\nimport json\n\nmetadata_line = json.dumps({\n    \"type\": \"darkfactory_metadata\",\n    \"task\": task_name,\n    \"model\": model,\n    \"success\": success,\n    \"exit_code\": exit_code,\n    \"failure_reason\": failure_reason,\n}) + \"\\n\"\n\nstdout_section = json.dumps({\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", \"section\": \"stdout\"}) + \"\\n\"\nstderr_section = json.dumps({\"type\": \"darkfactory_section\", \"section\": \"stderr\"}) + \"\\n\"\nstderr_line = json.dumps({\"type\": \"darkfactory_stderr\", \"text\": result.stderr}) + \"\\n\"\n```\n\nThen change the file extension from `.log` to `.jsonl` wherever the transient transcript path is constructed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: Transcripts written by `runner.py` are valid JSONL (every line parses as JSON).\n- [ ] AC-2: Transcript files use `.jsonl` extension in the transient location (`.harness-transcripts/{prd_id}.jsonl`).\n- [ ] AC-3: Metadata (task, model, success, exit_code, failure_reason) is present as a `darkfactory_metadata` JSONL line at the top of the file.\n- [ ] AC-4: Stdout content is preceded by a `darkfactory_section` line with `\"section\": \"stdout\"`.\n- [ ] AC-5: Stderr content is wrapped in a single `darkfactory_stderr` JSONL line.\n- [ ] AC-6: No `#`-prefixed comment lines remain in the transcript output.\n","numLines":84,"startLine":1,"totalLines":84}}}
