{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QDmhvEW2RShmCBti2H8a2E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both functions are only called in `invoke_claude`, and they operate on the subprocess stdout/agent_text, not on the transcript file. The darkfactory lines are only written to the transcript file after the subprocess completes.\n\nSo:\n1. `_find_terminal_result` would not misinterpret darkfactory lines because they'd check `type == \"result\"` which is false for darkfactory types\n2. `_parse_sentinels` wouldn't see darkfactory lines at all since it operates on subprocess stdout\n\nBUT: the PRD says to verify and update if necessary. Let me think about this more carefully...\n\n\nActually, I'm looking at how the transcript file is structured. The raw Claude Code stdout gets embedded inline between darkfactory section markers, so if `_find_terminal_result` were ever called on the full transcript contents, it would encounter both the darkfactory metadata lines and the original Claude Code events mixed together.\n\nThe darkfactory lines would get filtered out correctly since they don't have `type == \"result\"`, but the actual Claude Code result event would still be found and returned. However, there's a potential issue with `_parse_sentinels` — if it were called on transcript file content, it could accidentally match sentinel patterns inside darkfactory_stderr lines since the regex does substring matching. But in practice this shouldn't happen because `_parse_sentinels` is only ever called on subprocess stdout, not on transcript files.\n\nThe PRD is asking for a defensive filter anyway — if there's any risk that these functions might be called on transcript content in the future (like for recovery or debugging), we should add a check to exclude lines with `\"type\"` starting with `\"darkfactory_\"`. For `_parse_sentinels` specifically, since it takes a string and applies regex to it, a darkfactory_stderr line containing sentinel text could theoretically cause a false match.\n\nLooking at the PRD's suggested implementation, it shows per-line filtering with a JSON parse and type check, which implies the function should iterate over lines rather than operating on the full string as it currently does.\n\nThe most practical approach is to preprocess the stdout string to strip out darkfactory lines before passing it to `_parse_sentinels`, or restructure `_parse_sentinels` itself to handle line-by-line filtering. The key question is whether to filter at the call site in `invoke_claude` or within the parsing function itself. Adding defensive filters to both functions makes sense for robustness, even though the current data flow doesn't expose them to darkfactory lines. I'll add an explicit check in `_find_terminal_result` to exclude darkfactory types, and consider whether `_parse_sentinels` needs the same treatment for consistency. Filtering darkfactory envelope lines... I need to add a preprocessing step to filter out darkfactory lines before sentinel scanning, since those envelope lines could contain text that accidentally matches a sentinel pattern. For `_find_terminal_result`, the existing logic already protects it since it only returns objects where `type == \"result\"`, which darkfactory types can never be, but `_parse_sentinels` needs explicit protection.\n\nAdding preprocessing filter... I'm writing the filtering logic now...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":976,"cache_read_input_tokens":35207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":976},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3ac8cfa-47e5-4f0b-af2d-2bedae0776fa","uuid":"0707f6ed-2033-4046-bc9c-93d399ad7680"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QDmhvEW2RShmCBti2H8a2E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze:\n\n1. **`_find_terminal_result`**: Checks `obj.get(\"type\") == \"result\"`. Darkfactory types (`darkfactory_metadata`, `darkfactory_section`, `darkfactory_stderr`) don't match `\"result\"`, so safe — but can add explicit filter for defense-in-depth.\n\n2. **`_parse_sentinels`**: Uses regex on the full stdout string. If a `darkfactory_stderr` line contains sentinel text in its `text` field (e.g., wrapping stderr that captured a prior sentinel), the regex would match it — a real false-positive risk.\n\n3. **`.log` references**: Already confirmed none in invoke.py.\n\nLet me add the defensive guards:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":976,"cache_read_input_tokens":35207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":976},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3ac8cfa-47e5-4f0b-af2d-2bedae0776fa","uuid":"e7b8e458-ddc7-46b9-bd40-06d75d02774f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QDmhvEW2RShmCBti2H8a2E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015KT1S8XZZXkUnvWYNSG3xN","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-560.3-verify-invoke-parsing/src/darkfactory/invoke.py","old_string":"def _find_terminal_result(output_lines: list[str]) -> dict[str, Any] | None:\n    \"\"\"Scan output lines for the last {\"type\": \"result\", ...} JSON object.\"\"\"\n    for line in reversed(output_lines):\n        line = line.strip()\n        if not line.startswith(\"{\"):\n            continue\n        try:\n            obj: dict[str, Any] = json.loads(line)\n            if obj.get(\"type\") == \"result\":\n                return obj\n        except json.JSONDecodeError:\n            continue\n    return None","new_string":"def _find_terminal_result(output_lines: list[str]) -> dict[str, Any] | None:\n    \"\"\"Scan output lines for the last {\"type\": \"result\", ...} JSON object.\"\"\"\n    for line in reversed(output_lines):\n        line = line.strip()\n        if not line.startswith(\"{\"):\n            continue\n        try:\n            obj: dict[str, Any] = json.loads(line)\n            if obj.get(\"type\", \"\").startswith(\"darkfactory_\"):\n                continue\n            if obj.get(\"type\") == \"result\":\n                return obj\n        except json.JSONDecodeError:\n            continue\n    return None"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":976,"cache_read_input_tokens":35207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":976},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3ac8cfa-47e5-4f0b-af2d-2bedae0776fa","uuid":"c7b58e14-3341-421c-9d